# {{lb|en|Buddhism}} Any of the [[vehicle]]s of Buddhist or Tantric practice.
#* {{quote-book|en|2013|Chögyam Trungpa|editor=Judith L. Lief|The Bodhisattva Path of Wisdom and Compassion|volume=2|chapter=1|text=The Tibetan word for '''yana''' is ''thekpa'', which means "that which lifts you up." Anything that lifts you up and takes you to your destination is a '''yana'''.}}
